text\-safety\-scan\-find(1) \-\- Run text\-safety\-scan\-file across every file under a directory tree ==============================================================================================
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
\fBtext\-safety\-scan\-find\fR \fIPATH\fR [\fIfind\-expression\fR\|\.\|\.\|\.]
.P
\fBtext\-safety\-scan\-find\fR \fB\-\-help\fR
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Thin wrapper around \fBfind\fR(1) that hands every regular file under the given starting point(s) to \fBtext\-safety\-scan\-file\fR(1)\. The user controls recursion / pruning / symlink / size / binary policy by passing standard \fBfind\fR(1) expressions; this script does not invent a DSL\.
.P
The exact pipeline is:
.IP "" 4
.nf
find "$@" \-type f \-print0 | xargs \-0 \-r text\-safety\-scan\-file \-\-
.fi
.IP "" 0
.P
Anything before the trailing \fB\-type f \-print0\fR is passed verbatim to find\. See \fBfind\fR(1) for expression syntax\.
.SH "EXAMPLES"
Scan every file under \fB/repo\fR:
.IP "" 4
.nf
text\-safety\-scan\-find /repo
.fi
.IP "" 0
.P
Skip the \fB\.git\fR directory:
.IP "" 4
.nf
text\-safety\-scan\-find /repo \-not \-path '*/\.git/*'
.fi
.IP "" 0
.P
Skip image files:
.IP "" 4
.nf
text\-safety\-scan\-find /repo \-not \-name '*\.png' \-not \-name '*\.jpg'
.fi
.IP "" 0
.P
Follow symlinks (default is to NOT follow):
.IP "" 4
.nf
text\-safety\-scan\-find \-L /repo
.fi
.IP "" 0
.P
Limit to small files only:
.IP "" 4
.nf
text\-safety\-scan\-find /repo \-size \-1M
.fi
.IP "" 0
.P
Combine prunes with size filter:
.IP "" 4
.nf
text\-safety\-scan\-find /repo \-not \-path '*/\.git/*' \-size \-1M
.fi
.IP "" 0
.SH "EXIT CODES"
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fB0\fR All scanned files are clean\.
.IP "\(bu" 4
non\-zero An error occurred or a finding was reported\. The exact exit code is whatever the \fBfind\fR(1) / \fBxargs\fR(1) / \fBtext\-safety\-scan\-file\fR(1) pipeline produced; this wrapper does not translate it\. Notably, \fBxargs\fR collapses any child exit code in \fB1\.\.125\fR to its own \fB123\fR, so the per\-finding\-vs\-hard\-error distinction the file tool makes is lost here\. For maintainers who need that fidelity, run \fBtext\-safety\-scan\-file\fR(1) on individual files\.
.IP "" 0
.SH "NOTES"
.IP "\(bu" 4
Paths starting with \fB\-\fR are not handled here; they would confuse \fBfind\fR(1)'s argument parser\. If you need to scan such a path, prepend \fB\./\fR to the path or use \fBtext\-safety\-scan\-file\fR(1) directly with \fB\-\-\fR\.
.IP "\(bu" 4
This wrapper is deliberately five lines of bash\. Read the source if you want to know exactly what it does\.
.IP "" 0
